race.comment: KITTY OKAY (10) was very good first-up at Canterbury last campaign but failed to land the knockout blow through May and June. She's been readied for this preparation with a nice trial at Kembla and her figures from last campaign stand out. Maps beautifully and can land the knockout blow this time. TOP SPEED (8) has been chasing the riches of Super Maiden's recently, finishing well back at Nowra before a 1.7L defeat when sitting on the speed throughout at Taree most recently. Draws a better gate this time around and this looks a much easier race on paper. Can get the job done. LINDOS (13) is a daughter of G1 winner Linky Dink on debut. She trialled well behind handy 2YO galloper Masvingo recently and her siblings have had good success on the racecourse. Can make an impact right away. PARIAH TIME (7) was hard to run down in a strong maiden here 11 days ago. Won't be far away again. C'MON WICKSY (1) has to be included first-up.
